    • Method Detail

      • loadKeyStore

        public static java.security.KeyStore loadKeyStore​(java.util.function.Supplier<java.security.Provider[]> providers,
                                                  java.lang.String providerName,
                                                  java.io.FileInputStream is,
                                                  java.lang.String filename,
                                                  char[] password)
                                           throws java.io.IOException,
                                                  java.security.KeyStoreException
        Tries to parse a keystore based on known recognizable patterns. This method can parse JKS, JCEKS, PKCS12, BKS, BCFKS and UBER key stores. At first the method looks for recognizable patterns of JKS, JCEKS, PKCS12 and BKS key store types and tries to parse them if found. If the patter recognition failed, brute force is used to load the key store. The provider supplier is used for loading the key stores.
        Parameters:
        providers - provider supplier for loading the keystore (must not be null)
        providerName - if specified only providers with this name will be used
        is - the key store file input stream (must not be null)
        filename - the filename for prioritizing brute force checks using the file extension
        password - password of the key store
        Returns:
        loaded key store if recognized
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
        java.security.KeyStoreException
